    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` Namespace\n\nThe implementation follows the exact same 5-layer architecture used by `Bun.TOML`, `Bun.YAML`, `Bun.JSON5`, and `Bun.JSONC`.\n\n### 9 Files to Create/Modify\n\n**2 new files:**\n1. **`src/interchange/ini.zig`** — Self-contained INI parser (returns `ast.Expr`) and `Stringifier` struct. Handles sections (`[name]`), `key=value` pairs, `;`/`#` comment lines, type inference (numbers/booleans), quoted strings, and dot-notation section names (`[outer.inner]`). Does NOT import `src/ini.zig`.\n2. **`src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** — JS API layer with `create()`, `parse()`, and `stringify()`, modeled on `JSON5Object.zig`.\n\n**7 existing files modified** (minimal, surgical edits each):\n3. `src/interchange.zig` — add `pub const ini = @import(...)` (1 line)\n4. `src/bun.js/api.zig` — add `pub const INIObject = @import(...)` (1 line)\n5. `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` — 4 locations: struct constant, `exportAll()` export, getter function, bottom import\n6. `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` — add `macro(INI)` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER`\n7. `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` — add `INI` row to the `@begin bunObjectTable`\n8. `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` — add `namespace INI` with JSDoc + `parse` and `stringify` signatures\n\n**1 new test file:**\n9. `test/js/bun/ini/ini-api.test.ts` — tests for `Bun.INI.parse` and `Bun.INI.stringify` (distinct from the existing `ini.test.ts` which tests the internal npm INI parser)",
